November 10, 1969 No. 1173,

October Term, 1968.

Jones v. Illinois By Its Electoral Board, William J. Scott, Attorney General of Illinois, and Francis T. Crowe, Herman Tavins, and A. Zola Groves, Assistant Attorneys General, in opposition.

395 U. S. 162. Motion to require state and local officials of Illinois promptly to conduct an election for office of Lieutenant Governor of Illinois denied.

The Chief Justice took no part in the consideration or decision of this motion.
